<h3>Introduction</h3>

<p>Huxtable is a package for creating HTML and LaTeX tables. It provides similar
functionality to xtable, but more, with a simpler interface. Here's a quick example.
</p>

<!--begin.rcode echo = TRUE, results = 'asis'


ht <- hux(
        Employee = c('John Smith', 'Jane Doe', 'David Hugh-Jones'),
        Salary = c(50000, 50000, 40000),
        add_colnames = TRUE
      )

bold(ht)[1,]           <- TRUE
bottom_border(ht)[1,]  <- TRUE
align(ht)[,2]          <- 'right'
right_padding(ht)      <- 10
left_padding(ht)       <- 10
width(ht)              <- 0.35

ht
end.rcode-->


<p>To learn more, check out the vignette in <a href="introduction-to-huxtable.html">HTML</a> or <a href="introduction-to-huxtable.pdf">PDF</a> format, or the original <a href="introduction-to-huxtable.Rmd">R Markdown</a>.</p>

